@{
}
<br />
<div class="row">
    <div class="col-1"></div>
    <div class="col-6 text-center">
        <div class="timeline-panel pl-1">
            <div class="timeline-heading pl-2">
                <h3>Predicted Crash Severity : @ViewBag.improper_restraint</h3>
                <h6 class="subheading">
                    @if (ViewBag.seatbelt == "1")
                    {<p>Minor accident with no injuries</p>}
                    else if (ViewBag.seatbelt == "2")
                    {<p>Minor accident with possible injuries</p>}
                    else if (ViewBag.seatbelt == "3")
                    {<p>Accident with minor injuries</p>}
                    else if (ViewBag.seatbelt == "4")
                    {<p>Accident with serious injuries</p>}
                    else
                    {<p>Major accident with one or more fatalities</p>}
                </h6>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-body"><p class="text-muted">“Properly worn” seat belts mean both straps are snugly fitted to your hipbones and shoulder bones, not cutting across either the stomach or neck. <br /><br />Injuries to the spinal cord, abdomen, and shoulders occur as a result of improper seatbelt use. <a href="https://www.focusphysiotherapy.com/physical-dangers-wearing-seatbelts-improperly/">Common injuries</a> include dislocations, fractures, and internal bleeding.
</p></div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-5 text-center my-auto">
        <img class="border border-1" width=80% src="/assets/img/improper.png" />
    </div>
</div>
<br />